(firstQuint)Non-Invasive Characterization in Cardiac Sarcoidosis.

 Cardiac sarcoidosis is a serious medical condition which affects the heart.

 The purpose of this study is to characterize the relationship between the FDG PET findings and other markers of inflammation including using a new targeted PET radiotracer, 11C-PBR28, and analysis of blood specimens.

